            . I am a watchman. I saw the prisoner coming out of the house at half-past three o'clock in the morning, with these things under his jacket - he asked the time - I asked what he had got; he said it belonged to his wife.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. A young man there gave it me to take to the Royal Oak public-house, Thames-street.</p>
